"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"Imagine this.\\n\\nIt’s 11 a.m., and the heat is oppressive. We’re both enjoying cold coffee in a cafe at Connaught Place having a conversation about books. We see a person who looks physically sound but is obese.\\n\\nHis table is piled high with all the crap the cafe has to offer. Sandwiches, pastries, bagels, donuts, and anything else that an obese person should not consume.\\n\\n“What do you think the person lacks?” I’d ask.\\n\\nYour response would be something along the lines of\\n\\n*   “Doesn’t take care of his health”\\n*   “Consumes a lot of junk”\\n*   “Doesn’t work out often”\\n*   “Might have some health issues”\\n\\nYou see, our brain is very similar to this. Information is like food. **Our mental obesity is determined by the type of information we consume.**\\n\\nAnd, with the way the world is, if you don’t make an effort to protect yourself from the constant barrage of meaningless information, you’ll end up like the overweight person sitting at the cafe eating junk.\\n\\nSomething fascinating I’ve seen is that when you start curating for others, you grow better at consuming.\\n\",\"timestamp\":1640779822,\"title\":\"7 | Mental Obesity\"},\"digest\":\"dWiJ5A8DfSjjxb94dnFqZIb99bq1lEspqTfIYMwXKqU\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x5937B6F2AC85472ADD93e1B9625ecC2e14691079\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"h5lpeTZi610re7saoRElaSwAjcYRP38MDJfigCe-g5c\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"-vE5DPfbiCwGnQ5tkrVOi2TwdWXS-e3dmcxUTVLU6Pg\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"i2XJ0vjHVqx3weK_6vLzRkMxGvfsW4_9KfKGOodzaHRr2DT6-qh3uvsQiECYji6nSx6Fj8BhrICbjLRE8FhYyQ\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xbffde3def1b5ccce71faa882a3d58409061eeebee28d5883a4caf8069077f1ad0418113a5238fb673ece9f4d9ae58790a805084b5df3cdf76f18edd30d6b08961b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"ve